heaviest_rainfall.status: The storm today is ranked 7th for the amount of rainfall recorded during one storm.  23.86mm fell at a maximum rate of 8.3mm per hour over 31.0 hours.  On 09 November 2025, a record rainfall of 47.89mm was measured, indicating an exceptionally wet day.  24.6mm per hour was recorded as falling at times during the 144.8 hour storm.

heaviest_rainrate.status: 34.3mm per hour is the maximum rain rate ever recorded on 02 September 2025, during a 15.0 hour storm which dumped 21.19mm of rain from the clouds.

longest_rain.status: Ranked 7th for lengthiest precipitation event, today's storm spanned 31.0 hours and was characterized by a peak rain intensity of 8.3mm per hour.  23.86mm of rain fell in total.  On 09 November 2025, the rain lasted for 144.8 hours, which is the longest time recorded by our database.  47.89mm accumulated and it fell at 24.6mm per hour at times.
